other_tests.findings: Well-defined multilobulated tumor in the dermis and subcutaneous tissue containing two types of epithelial cells arranged in intertwining cords and small lumina.
Severe and consistent hypernasality with nasal air emission on all speech sounds.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Improved speech immediately after the operation, considered normal at 1-year follow-up.
